headline: US STOCKS-Wall St extends gains as rate-cut hopes linger
summary: U.S. stock indexes rose on Tuesday, extending their recent run on expectations that the Federal Reserve will cut interest rates this year, while a drop in shares of Walt Disney following the company's quarterly results limited their gains.  Walt Disney fell 8.4% in early trading, as a surprise profit in its streaming entertainment division was eclipsed by a drop in its traditional TV business and weaker box office.
